cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Compute-and-Forward is a technique to deal with interference in wireless communication systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a technique to improve the performance of wireless networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with improving the performance of wireless networks, which can be seen as a social network of devices communicating with each other. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an algorithm to solve the Shortest Lattice Vector (SLV) problem, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of the SLV problem and proposes an algorithm to solve it, which falls under the scope of computational complexity.
